Typhoon Fanapi has killed 70 people
and left 65 people missing in Chinaâ€™s southern province of
Guangdong, Xinhua News Agency said, citing provincial flood-
control authorities.  The death tally rose after work crews entered towns cut off
by mudslides, Xinhua said. About 99,500 people were displaced by
the storm, 3,765 houses were destroyed, 42,190 hectares of
farmland damaged and the economic loss increased to 2.4 billion
